div.h2: Token Bucket Rate Limiter Redis INCR + EXPIRE Algorithm
div.p: IP: 203.0.113.1 Route: shorten Limit: 10 req / Window: 60 s
Key format: rl:{route}:{ip} Separates counters per route IP.
Atomicity Note: Lua script runs atomically server-side EXPIRE fires only once, when current==1.
Why val == 1 matters: TTL is set only on the first request to define the fixed window duration.
Fail-Open Invariant: Redis unavailability must NEVER block traffic. (Spec M5 1)
Lua vs Pipeline: Atomic INCR + EXPIRE No race on TTL creation One roundtrip
